{"word":"οἰχνέω","slug":"οἰχνέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>οἰχνέω</b></el> <el>(οἰχνέω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> and ionic <a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a> <el>οἴχνεσκον</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to go, come</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; <i>to walk</i>, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> <i>to live</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>like <el>οἴχομαι</el>, <i>to be gone</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a>, like <el>προσέρχομαι</el>, <i>to approach</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}